The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	Bangalore, June 11: A security guard from Bengals Midnapore was arrested for allegedly stealing the credit card of his companys boss and withdrawing up to Rs 1.5 lakh.          
	Kalyan Topno, 22, had stolen the card of managing director Satish Kumar, who did not know about the theft till he received a bank statement last week.          Poring over the details, he spotted five ATM withdrawals to the tune of Rs 1.5 lakh over the past month. He then began looking for the card but did not find it.          Topno stole the card from Kumars office drawer and found the ATM pin scrawled on the signature panel, police said.                  
	Tumkur (PTI): Twenty students of a girls hostel in Karnataka fell sick after inhaling chlorine gas, which leaked from a tank on Wednesday. The Tumkur municipal authorities had stored the gas in a tank. Police blamed lack of safety measures for the leak.                  
	Rajkot (PTI): A labourer was killed in an explosion at a steel production company in Gujarat, police said on Wednesday. Alam Anjar was seriously injured when a barrel burst in a fabrication unit of Vikram Steel Plant where welding work was on. He was declared dead in hospital. The police are probing the cause of the explosion.                  
	Ahmednagar (PTI): An elderly farmer died in Maharashtra on Tuesday after his farming equipment came in contact with a high tension wire while he was ploughing his field, police said. Villagers accused the electric distribution company of negligence and demanded compensation for the family of the victim.                  
	 Ahmedabad (PTI): Sujatpur village of Mehsana district in Gujarat was flooded on Wednesday following a breach in the Narmada canal lining, police said. Rescue operations are on and the villagers are being evacuated. A probe is on to find out the cause of the breach.
                                                                                                                         
